quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  79,1,By those who tear it out with violence
  79,2,By those who gently draw it out
  79,3,And by those who glide along
  79,4,Then press forward as in a race
  79,5,And plan to do it
  79,6,One day all that can be in commotion will be in violent commotion
  79,7,Followed by repeated commotions
  79,8,Hearts that day will be in agitation
  79,9,Their eyes will be caste down
  79,10,"They say, “What, will we indeed be returned to our former state"
  79,11,"“What, when we will have become decayed bones?”"
  79,12,"They say, “It would, in that case, be a return with loss.”"
  79,13,"But indeed, it will be but a single cry"
  79,14,"When behold, they will be in the awakening"
  79,15,Has the story of Moses reached you
  79,16,"Behold, your Lord called to him in the sacred valley of Tuwa"
  79,17,"“Go to Pharaoh, for he has indeed transgressed all bounds"
  79,18,"“And say to him, ‘Do you want to be purified"
  79,19,"“And that I guide you to your Lord, so you can fear Him?”"
  79,20,Then Moses showed him the great sign
  79,21,But he rejected it and did not follow
  79,22,"Further, he turned his back, striving hard"
  79,23,Then he gathered them and made a proclamation
  79,24,"Saying, “I am your Lord, Most High”"
  79,25,"But God punished him, and made an example of him, in the hereafter, and in the present life"
  79,26,Indeed in this is an instructive warning for whoever is conscious of God